text: The United Methodist Church of Sweden () was a Christian denomination in Sweden. It existed between 1868 and 2012. It contributed towards the creation of the Uniting Church in Sweden. According to a report from 2009, the denomination had 6,436 members. ==References== ==Other websites== *Former website Category:1868 establishments in Europe Category:2012 disestablishments in Sweden Category:Methodism Category:Protestantism in Sweden Category:19th- century establishments in Sweden
